HEADWORD: Planorbis
<hw>Pla*nor"bis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>planus</ets> flat + <ets>orbis</ets> a circle.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any fresh-water air-breathing mollusk belonging
to <gen>Planorbis</gen> and other allied genera, having shells of a
discoidal form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

